observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the City Mayor instruct:

21. Maintain the PPELCs;

22.Undertake collaborative procedures with the CGS Officer to ensure that all PPEs included in the RPCPPE are duly recorded; 

23. The Inventory Committee to conduct complete inventory count of all PPE items; and

24. The CGS Officer and the City Accountant, to conduct periodic reconciliation of the property and accounting records.

We recommended that the City Accountant:
Draw the necessary journal entry vouchers (JEVs) to record the valid book reconciling items;
Coordinate with the City Treasurer to conduct a thorough review of the unidentified reconciling items reflected in the BRS for its proper adjustments and support the same with relevant documentary evidence;
Monitor the status of accounts in the books and immediately take actions to avoid its dormancy/idleness; and
Submit monthly BRS with complete supporting documents.
We also recommended that the City Treasurer closely coordinate with the City Accountant and take immediate action for any dormant bank account under custody.

We recommended that management ensure that all insurable assets and properties are adequately covered/insured with the General Insurance Fund of the GSIS by performing the following:
Prepare the Property Inventory Form (PIF) listing of all the insurable properties and other assets, showing their latest appraised values/valuation, appraisal date, location, and other information;
Extract from the Report on the Physical Count of PPE, as well as from the Report of the Physical Count of Inventories, the data for the PIF pertaining to the insurable assets and interests of the government;
Cause the appraisal of the insurable properties and other assets through in-house appraisal for properties or insurable interests with a value of P10 million and below, and through independent appraisal for properties with insurable interest exceeding ₱10 million;
Submit the consolidated PIF to the Supervising Auditor/Audit Team Leader and the GIF, GSIS, not later than April 30 of each year; and
Include in the agency annual budget the amount of premiums for the general insurance covering all insurable properties and other asserts and ensure its payment to the GSIS.
